Document: Requirements Specification
Title: Link Collection Rust - Requirements
Version: 1.0

SECTION: System Requirements

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-001
Title: Read existing database files
Statement: |-
  The system shall support reading and processing existing database files
  to retrieve link collection data.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-002
Title: Create a CLI application
Statement: |-
  The system shall provide a command-line interface with top-level commands
  and multiple subcommands for managing link collections.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-003
Title: Add a new record to the database
Statement: |-
  The system shall allow users to add new records to the database through
  the CLI and temporary file uploads.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-004
Title: Retrieve items from database
Statement: |-
  The system shall support retrieval and querying of items from the database.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-005
Title: Download items from HackerNews
Statement: |-
  The system shall download link items from HackerNews and persist them
  to the database with publication date metadata.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-006
Title: Create a wrapper on top of recutils library
Statement: |-
  The system shall provide a wrapper abstraction over the recutils library
  for database operations.
Status: Active

REQUIREMENT: SYSREQ-007
Title: Replace Go Stubs with Rust Stubs
Statement: |-
  The system shall migrate from Go-based stub implementations to pure Rust
  stub implementations for all external dependencies.
Status: Active

SECTION: High-Level Requirements

REQUIREMENT: HLR-001-1
Title: Dump the contents into the console
Statement: |-
  The system shall be able to read database files and output their contents
  to the console for inspection and debugging.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-001
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-001-2
Title: Use a fixed template to print to console
Statement: |-
  The system shall support printing database contents using a predefined
  template format for consistent output.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-001
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-001-3
Title: Use any template to print to console
Statement: |-
  The system shall allow users to specify custom templates for printing
  database contents to the console.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-001
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-001-4
Title: Read the existing date formats
Statement: |-
  The system shall parse and handle multiple date formats present in
  existing database files.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-001
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-001-5
Title: Add the optional field 'Link'
Statement: |-
  The system shall support reading and processing the optional 'Link'
  field from database records.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-001
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-006-1
Title: Use clap for top command and multiple subcommands
Statement: |-
  The system shall use the clap crate for command-line argument parsing
  to support hierarchical commands and subcommands.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-002
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-006-2
Title: Add a logger
Statement: |-
  The system shall include logging functionality for debugging and tracing
  application execution.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-002
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-006-3
Title: Add a configuration system
Statement: |-
  The system shall provide configuration management to avoid repeating
  hardcoded values throughout the application.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-002
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-006-4
Title: Read the configuration from a file
Statement: |-
  The system shall read configuration values from TOML files with support
  for multiple sources and priority levels.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-002
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-006-5
Title: List the tags from the database
Statement: |-
  The system shall provide a command to list all tags present in the
  database with counts and metadata.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-002
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-002-1
Title: Add record from the CLI
Statement: |-
  The system shall allow users to add new records to the database through
  command-line interface input.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-003
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-002-2
Title: Add record from a temporary file
Statement: |-
  The system shall allow users to add new records to the database from
  temporary file uploads.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-003
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-002-3
Title: Print the record in the same order as it was provided
Statement: |-
  The system shall maintain and respect the original field order when
  printing records that were added to the database.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-003
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-004-1
Title: Create a new stubbed HTTP server
Statement: |-
  The system shall include a stubbed HTTP server for testing HackerNews
  download functionality.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-005
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-004-2
Title: Download the items from a URL
Statement: |-
  The system shall fetch link items from a given HackerNews URL endpoint
  and parse the response.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-005
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-004-3
Title: Commit to git using the date of publishing
Statement: |-
  The system shall create git commits for downloaded HackerNews items
  using their original publication date as the commit date.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-005
Status: Approved

REQUIREMENT: HLR-007-1
Title: Create Rust Stubs for existing Go Stubs
Statement: |-
  The system shall replace all Go stub implementations with equivalent
  Rust implementations without changing external behavior.
ParentReq: SYSREQ-007
Status: Approved

SECTION: Low-Level Requirements - Configuration Management

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-1
Title: Configuration file in TOML format
Statement: |-
  Configuration files shall use TOML format for human readability and
  structured data representation.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-2
Title: Read config from user home directory
Statement: |-
  The system shall read configuration from ~/.config/lc/config.toml
  as the default configuration location.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-3
Title: Read config from .env.local file
Statement: |-
  The system shall support overriding configuration values from a
  .env.local file in the current working directory.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-4
Title: Read config from environment variable
Statement: |-
  The system shall support overriding configuration via LC_CONFIG_FILE
  environment variable.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-5
Title: Read config from command line argument
Statement: |-
  The system shall support overriding configuration via --config-file
  command-line argument.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-6
Title: Configuration contains database_file
Statement: |-
  Configuration shall include database_file field specifying the path
  to the database file.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-7
Title: Configuration contains log_level
Statement: |-
  Configuration shall include log_level field specifying the logging level.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-8
Title: Configuration contains template_file
Statement: |-
  Configuration shall include template_file field specifying the path
  to the output template file.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-9
Title: Configuration contains hacker_news_url
Statement: |-
  Configuration shall include hacker_news_url field specifying the URL
  for HackerNews item downloads.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-10
Title: Create struct to hold configuration values
Statement: |-
  A struct shall be created to hold all configuration values with proper
  type definitions and defaults.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-11
Title: Implement configuration file merging
Statement: |-
  The system shall merge configuration values from multiple sources
  respecting priority order.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-12
Title: Include configuration in logging setup
Statement: |-
  The logger shall be configured using the log_level from configuration.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-13
Title: Include configuration in database connection
Statement: |-
  Database connection logic shall use the database_file from configuration.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-14
Title: Include configuration in template rendering
Statement: |-
  Template rendering logic shall use the template_file from configuration.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4

REQUIREMENT: LLR-006-4-15
Title: Include configuration in HackerNews download
Statement: |-
  HackerNews download logic shall use the hacker_news_url from configuration.
ParentReq: HLR-006-4
